---
import { getEntry } from "astro:content";

import { getPageById } from "../config/site-manifest";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const aboutPage = getPageById("about");
const aboutSeo = await getEntry("pages", "about");

if (!aboutPage) {
  throw new Error("Could not find the 'about' page config.");
}

if (!aboutSeo) {
  throw new Error("Could not find the 'about' page metadata.");
}
---

<BaseLayout
  page={aboutPage}
  seo={aboutSeo.data}
  mainClass="site-main site-main--about"
>
  <section class="about-page">
    <section class="about-hero" aria-labelledby="about-title">
      <h1 id="about-title">Why we built Bolus</h1>
      <p class="about-hero__dek">Paper charting should not still be the standard.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="about-manifesto" aria-label="About Bolus">
      <p>
        Paper is still common in office-based anesthesia, even though it creates exactly the kinds
        of problems modern tools should remove. Handwriting adds ambiguity. Scattered pages slow
        everything down. The final record often looks worse than the care behind it.
      </p>

      <p>
        We built Bolus because the standard should feel higher than that. Documentation should be
        clean, legible, and fast enough to keep up with the case. The record should feel easier to
        create in the moment and easier to stand behind later.
      </p>

      <p>
        Bolus is intentionally focused. It is not trying to become bloated practice software with
        every administrative feature bolted on. It is built to do one job well: help office-based
        providers replace paper with a more serious, modern documentation workflow.
      </p>

      <p>
        Cleaner records. Less ambiguity. Higher standards.
      </p>

      <p class="about-manifesto__signoff">Pressor Systems LLC</p>
    </section>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
